        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 5:04PM EDT by NWS Wilmington NC</headline>
        <description>At 502 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Butters to Elizabethtown to near Harrells
to near White Stocking. Movement was northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph. Torrential rainfall is also
occurring with these storms and may lead to localized
flooding.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Burgaw, Elizabethtown, Rowan, Bladenboro, Penderlea, Point Caswell,
Maple Hill, Bladen Community College, Ammon, Butters, Ashton, Currie,
Wards Corner, White Oak, White Stocking, Smiths, Duart, Tolarsville,
Abbottsburg, and Lisbon.

This includes Interstate 40 between mile markers 388 and 407.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building. Do not
drive your vehicle through flooded roadways. Continuous cloud to
ground lightning is occurring with these storms.Lightning is one of
nature's leading killers.</instruction>
